gomodel:SYNGO_736  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig. S2e; biochemical fractionation showe that LRRTM3 is enriched in the PSD fraction\nFig. S2f,g,h,i; endogenous LRRTM3 colocalizes with PSD-95 and VGLUT1 but not with Gephyrin and GAD67 in hippocampal cultures\nFig. S2k; in hippocampal cultured neurons overexpressed Venus-LRRTM3 colocalize with VGLUT1 and PSD-95.\n\nLiteral:\n\"Notably, L3L was enriched in detergent-resistant PSD fractions (Figure S2E). These data indicate\nthat LRRTM3 (at least L3L) is associated with excitatory synaptic membranes. In accord with biochemical data, confocal microscopy revealed that L3L immunoreactivity was closely associated with the excitatory marker proteins VGLUT1 and PSD-95, but not with the inhibitory marker proteins GAD67 and gephyrin in cultured hippocampal neurons (Figures S2F-S2J). L3L immunoreactivity was also prominent outside VGLUT1- or PSD-95-positive excitatory synaptic sites, consistent with its widespread distribution in various subcellular fractions (see Figure S2D). To corroborate these observations, we expressed monomeric Venus (mVenus) fluorescent protein fused to L3L (L3L-mVenus) in cultured hippocampal neurons and immunostained them for VGLUT1 and PSD-95 (Figure S2K). mVenus immunofluorescence in L3L-mVenus-expressing neurons was clustered at excitatory synapse sites (55% ± 5% and 49% ± 6% of L3L-mVenus-positive puncta matches with PSD-95 and VGLUT1, respectively), suggesting that endogenous L3L proteins, similar to L3S, localize to excitatory synapses\"\n\n8/6/2017 Pim\n- LRRTM3 has TM domain --> \"integral component ....\"\n- Localization to the postsynaptic density membrane is supported (not demonstrated) by the PPI with PSD-95 protein.. Experimental description: LRRTM3 colocalization with excitatory synapse markers was performed in rat hippocampal cultures. Hovever biochemical fractionation was performed in mouse brain.\n\nLiteral from Supplemetary M&M\n\"Cultured hippocampal neurons were prepared from E18 rat brains, as described previously\"\n\"Postsynaptic density Fractions. The PSD fraction was prepared as described previously (Dosemeci et al., 2006). Briefly, mouse brains were homogenized in 0.32 M\"\nsucrose/1 mM MgCl2 containing a protease inhibitor cocktail (Thermo Scientific) using a Teflon/glass\nhomogenizer\n\n7/6/2017 Pim\n- species of the over-expressed LRRTM3 is **human**. Lietral Suppl,M&M: \"pGW1-LRRTM3[Long]-mVenus\nencodes full-length human LRRTM3 fused to mVenus ... Full-length LRRTM3\n(LRRTM3[Long] and LRRTM3[Short]) and LRRTM4 (LRRTM4[Long] and LRRTM4[Short]),\nexcluding the corresponding signal peptide sequences, were PCR-amplified,...\"\n- In terms of species selection I choose mouse over the other species based on the use of the biochem fract data in support of the selected term." , "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099061 replaced by GO:0098839" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0662-9523" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2949-9725" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_736" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

